      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static FredOutVal chooseBest(java.util.ArrayList<FredOutVal> values, java.io.File debug, MasterVariables masterVariables)
      Takes in a list of FredOutVal objects, chooses the first column from the right with a non-zero likelihood (ie first it tries 1.05x, 1.1x, then 1.25x, etc, and then sorts the objects by that value, using the greater likelihoods as tiebreakers, and outputs the best Fred Value from that sort pre - values is a list of appropriate fredoutvals and debug is a valid output filename post - the best FredOutVal is returned and the sorted list is written to debug

    • Method Detail

      • chooseBest

        public static FredOutVal chooseBest(java.util.ArrayList<FredOutVal> values,
                    java.io.File debug,
                    MasterVariables masterVariables)
        Takes in a list of FredOutVal objects, chooses the first column from the right with a non-zero likelihood (ie first it tries 1.05x, 1.1x, then 1.25x, etc, and then sorts the objects by that value, using the greater likelihoods as tiebreakers, and outputs the best Fred Value from that sort pre - values is a list of appropriate fredoutvals and debug is a valid output filename post - the best FredOutVal is returned and the sorted list is written to debug
        Parameters:
        values - The output from a run of Fred's method.
        debug - An output file to write the sorted list of values to, in case the chosen value was not optimal and the user wants to go back and see what other values might be used.
        Returns:
        FredOutVal containing the optimal choice for hill climbing.
